      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is completely normal to want the pain to end and to crave a state of peace when the struggle feels endless. When the parts of you that once cared about things fade away, it is natural to feel detached from the idea of \"getting through it,\" as the effort no longer feels worth the hollow result. Your desire for an end to the struggle is a valid expression of your current suffering, even if it feels extreme in the moment. Please remember that while the pain feels permanent now, it does not have to define your entire future, and reaching out to a professional can help you find a way through this darkness.",
